    • connections

      private boolean[] connections
      Array that indicates if there is a side of the path in a specific direction.
      For the current version of the game, we have used the following order: {left, top, right, bottom}.
      If a value is true, this means that such a direction is part (input/output, i.e. side) of the path.

    • getAvailableConnections

      public java.util.EnumSet<Direction> getAvailableConnections()
      Returns a EnumSet with the directions/sides in which the road exists, e.g. {LEFT, RIGHT} for an HORIZONTAL road and {UP,DOWN} for a VERTICAL road.
      Returns:

    • map2CellType

      public static CellType map2CellType​(char fileSymbol)
      Given a Unicode character from a configuration file, it returns the CellType object.
      Parameters:
      fileSymbol - Symbol of the cell in the level/configuration file.
      Returns:
      It returns the CellType of the cell from a Symbol level. If the Unicode character does not exist, then it returns null.

    • next

      public abstract CellType next()
      This method is overridden by each CellType's value in order to say which is the next cell type so that a clockwise order is established, e.g. bottom-right -> bottom-left.
      Returns:
      Next cell type for the cell type that invokes this method.
